The paper deals with a graph modification problem, specifically the Interval Completion problem, which involves adding edges to a given graph to make it an interval graph. This problem is relevant to several areas of computer science, including data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational geometry (cs.CG), graph theory (cs.GT), and complexity theory (cs.CC). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
